<paragraph blockId="12.[747,1397,1400,1854]" box="[747,1397,1400,1424]" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">
<subSubSection box="[747,1214,1400,1424]" pageId="12" pageNumber="94" type="nomenclature">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[747,1214,1400,1424]" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">
7. An overlooked species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1066,1214,1400,1424]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Somalia">
sect. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1124,1214,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">Somalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
– The following 
<paragraph blockId="12.[747,1397,1400,1854]" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">
species has hitherto been overlooked for the area of “Flore d’Afrique centrale’; it was described from D.R.Congo, Katanga, but has been only known from the holotype, kept in BM; there is no isotype in BR, nor any other specimen identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Moore (Moore" authorityYear="1909" box="[840,973,1551,1575]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kaessneri">
<emphasis box="[840,973,1551,1575]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">B. kaessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in K or BR. Several specimens of that species were although found in the unidentified material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1789" box="[747,883,1611,1635]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="94" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="family">Acanthaceae</taxonomicName>
in both Herbaria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[747,1397,1400,1854]" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Moore (Moore" authorityYear="1909" box="[785,918,1649,1673]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kaessneri">
<emphasis box="[785,918,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">B. kaessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1195,1649,1673]" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1108,1195,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">Somalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, characterized i.a. by leaves of a distinct blue-green colour and beaked capsules. Close allies like 
<emphasis box="[920,1093,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">B. benguellensis</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1143,1284,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">B. calophylla</emphasis>
are placed in that section by 
<bibRefCitation box="[949,1255,1739,1764]" pageId="12" pageNumber="94" refId="ref9206" refString="Balkwill M. - J., Balkwill K. (1997) Delimitation and infrageneric classification of Barleria (Acanthaceae). Kew Bulletin 52: 535 - 573. [available at http: // www. jstor. org / pss / 4110286]" type="journal article">Balkwill &amp; Balkwill (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, which were unable to get sufficient material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Moore (Moore" authorityYear="1909" box="[1114,1244,1770,1794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kaessneri">
<emphasis box="[1114,1244,1770,1794]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="94">B. kaessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to place it satisfactorily in their classification (
<bibRefCitation pageId="12" pageNumber="94" refId="ref9206" refString="Balkwill M. - J., Balkwill K. (1997) Delimitation and infrageneric classification of Barleria (Acanthaceae). Kew Bulletin 52: 535 - 573. [available at http: // www. jstor. org / pss / 4110286]" type="journal article">Balkwill &amp; Balkwill 1997: 571</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
